item.description:
5. Executing from file #  Executing Wren code can also be done in the following ways:
// Same as above, specify the module name but instead // of the source code you tell it where the file is located. vm.runFromFile(&#34;main&#34;, &#34;path/to/some/main.wren&#34;); // Run specific module. This module must be an existing file &#34;utils/libB.wren&#34; // in one or more look-up paths specified during creation of wren::Vm vm(...); vm.runFromModule(&#34;utils/libB&#34;); Note
The runFromModule depends on the lookup paths you pass into the wren::VM constructor.

